# Minimal SHACL shapes file used by SHACLValidator integration tests.
#
# One shape: every ex:Person must have at least one ex:name. Mirrors
# the smallest realistic SHACL constraint pattern (sh:minCount on a
# required property) so the test can show both a passing path (Alice
# has a name) and a failing path (Bob has no name) without bringing
# in the ASHRAE 223P shapes file (which is 537 KB and ASHRAE-licensed).
#
# Keep this file tiny — it exists only to exercise the engine, not to
# stand in for any real-world SHACL workflow.

@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix ex: <http://example.com/> .

ex:PersonShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ex:Person ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:name ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:message "Person needs at least one name." ;
    ] .
